    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3067157024" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3067157024" />
    <a title="Danny" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4700987-danny"><img alt="Danny" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1338082838p2/4700987.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3067157024?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Danny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Danny" href="/user/show/4700987-danny">Danny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/13144758-sorcerer-s-apprentice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4700987-danny?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4700987-danny?shelf=asian">asian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3067157024" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9774992478087665476">A perfect travelogue while living in this period of enforced lockdown. It led my mind to wander into places I would otherwise not ventured into. This book instilled a natural sense of wanderlust. Tahir Shah journeys through India subcontinent to find the most absurds of &apos;miracles&apos; (which are mostly nicely wrapped parlour tricks or/and the abuse of sophisticated chemistry applied in cunning ways). <br/><br/>It was only after mid-way of the read that it dawned on me that this is a non-fiction book! In my de</span>
  <span id="freeText9774992478087665476" style="display:none">A perfect travelogue while living in this period of enforced lockdown. It led my mind to wander into places I would otherwise not ventured into. This book instilled a natural sense of wanderlust. Tahir Shah journeys through India subcontinent to find the most absurds of 'miracles' (which are mostly nicely wrapped parlour tricks or/and the abuse of sophisticated chemistry applied in cunning ways). <br /><br />It was only after mid-way of the read that it dawned on me that this is a non-fiction book! In my defence, there were multiple instances that threw me off. Starting from how the story started; with a childhood memory of a visit by the author's guardian of his ancestral tomb (also how his interest in 'magic' was piqued). Followed by a tedious training regime by a sadistic 'sorcerer'. It was also hard to believe how gullible the author was, he was tricked/robbed/stolen from. If these incidents did indeed happen, he was perhaps the most ill-prepared travel-writer. Eek!<br /><br />The story really picked up after he departed from the confine of the training ground to commence his journey of observation. Interesting sub-stories and the later dissection of the multiple deceptions made the book thoroughly enjoyable. Some of the observations were highly memorable too; Including an unconventional way of treating asthmatic patients; the looped-economy where devotees travel the distance to a temple to have their head shaved (to atone for one's sins) that are later made into wigs; Or beggars in urban cities renting both spaces for their stage and babies as their malicious prop. <br /><br />What an adventure! I do miss having Tahir as a travel companion in this quest to find the most obscure.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9774992478087665476" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

